javax.money

Class AbstractContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.money.AbstractContext
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractQuery, AmountFormatContext, ConversionContext, CurrencyContext, MonetaryContext, ProviderContext, RoundingContext

    public abstract class AbstractContext
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Represents a general context of data targeting an item of type Q. Contexts are used to add arbitrary data that cannot be be mapped in a standard way to the money API, e.g. use case or customer specific extensions os specialities.

    Superclasses of this class must be final, immutable, serializable and thread-safe.

    See Also:
    Serialized Form
